<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,940,1288]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1047,1072]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Comments:</emphasis>
in the first reference to this species, 
<bibRefCitation box="[757,900,1047,1072]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref16656" refString="Koch, C. L. (1847) System der Myriapoden. Panzer, H. - S., Kritische Revision der Insectenfauna Deutschlands, 3, 1 - 196." type="journal article">Koch (1847)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously identified it as 
<taxonomicName authority="Perty, 1833" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="scaber">
<emphasis box="[1219,1436,1047,1072]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Polydesmus scaber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[151,283,1084,1109]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref17384" refString="Perty, J. A. M. (1833) Delectus animalium articulatorum, quae in itinere per Brasiliam annis MDCCCXVII-MDCCCXX jussu et auspiciis Maximiliani Josephi I Bavariae Regis augustissimi peracto, collegerunt Dr. J. B. de Spix et Dr. C. F. Ph. de Martius. Fasc. III. Friedrich Fleischer, Munich, pp. 1 - 224." type="book chapter">Perty, 1833</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species in the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1895" box="[561,737,1084,1109]" class="Diplopoda" family="Chelodesmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chelodesmidae</taxonomicName>
. In his following work 
<bibRefCitation box="[1006,1149,1084,1109]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref16689" refString="Koch, C. L. (1863) Die Myriapoden. Getreu nach der Natur abgebildet und beschrieben. Bd. 1. H. W. Schmidt, Halle, 134 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10639" type="book">Koch (1863)</bibRefCitation>
omitted any reference to Perty's species, and so they have been treated as different taxa ever since. 
<bibRefCitation box="[991,1166,1119,1144]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref17978" refString="Silvestri, F. (1896) I Diplopodi. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Serie 2, 16, 121 - 254." type="journal article">Silvestri (1896)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Saussure &amp; Humbert" authorityYear="1872" box="[1301,1405,1119,1144]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Platyrhachis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scaber">
<emphasis box="[1301,1405,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">P. scaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the type species for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Hoffman" authorityYear="1960" box="[386,521,1156,1181]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Platyrhacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[386,521,1156,1181]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Platyrhacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Given the initial taxonomic uncertainty and to prevent possible nomenclatural problems at the genus and family level, 
<bibRefCitation box="[605,788,1191,1216]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref16238" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1974) Platyrhacus Koch, 1847 (Diplopoda). Petition for the designation by the international commission of a type-species in harmony with accustomed usage. Z. N. (S.) 2078. Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature, 31, 249 - 251." type="journal article">Hoffman (1974)</bibRefCitation>
proposed to change of type species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Hoffman" authorityYear="1960" box="[1229,1364,1191,1216]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Platyrhacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1364,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">Platyrhacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Javan 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch, 1847" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1847" box="[230,495,1228,1253]" class="Diplopoda" family="Platyrhacidae" genus="Platyrhacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis box="[230,334,1228,1252]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="259">P. fuscus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[352,495,1228,1253]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref16656" refString="Koch, C. L. (1847) System der Myriapoden. Panzer, H. - S., Kritische Revision der Insectenfauna Deutschlands, 3, 1 - 196." type="journal article">Koch, 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This proposal was accepted by the International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation box="[324,488,1263,1288]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref17216" refString="Melville, R. V. (1979) Opinion 1128. Platyrhacus Koch, 1847 (Diplopoda): designation of Platyrhacus fuscus Koch, 1847, as type species. Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature, 36, 73 - 75." type="journal article">Melville 1979</bibRefCitation>
). This species requires neotype designation (
<bibRefCitation box="[988,1170,1263,1288]" pageId="14" pageNumber="259" refId="ref16069" refString="Hoffman, R. L. (1953 a) A new Central American milliped of the genus Platyrhacus. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 55, 251 - 258." type="journal article">Hoffman 1953a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
